<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub126.ezboard.com/feqtraderscornersmithing.showMessage?topicID=5412.topic">pub126.ezboard.com/feqtra...5412.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
This is certainly a good news/bad news kinda thing, as banded and FS trivials are going to be lowered: good for people at lower levels looking for actually usable gear and bad for those who are currently in or a little passed banded and will need to do cultural or newer stuff to skillup. <br>
<br>
As I have two &quot;serious&quot; smith types this is what I'm going to do:<br>
<br>
a) Mathir: at 176 I can now only level on FS at 22p a combine (ouch!) and no cultural (either v1 or v2.) So, I will likely be trivial on FS after this goes in (or to most of it), so will be kinda sol (and I don't mean the new expansion.) No more smithing for skill for Mathir, hello Tailoring! (Wood Elves get cultural tailoring so the skill progession there is a bit more amenable to my race.) <br>
<br>
I will, however, be able to reliably make FS for my alts (and guilders!) so that's a verra verra nice thing. AC IS ALL!<br>
<br>
b) Cadip: at 156 is still mid-banded (Gaunts to 168 and then finish up with cloaks at 175.) Banded will likely be fully trivial to him after the patch, and maybe much of FS. He does have cultural (v1 and v2) to work on, so my plan is to try to get to 175 as fast as possible, while I can still level to there on cheap (2-4p) combines. I'll then have to shift to FS (maybe) and cultural (v1) to get any higher (but the cultural combines are drop heavy - gleep! - and comparable to FS plat wise - ouch!) I think that's generally a Good Thing, so will likely just need to start thinking of Cadip as &quot;my smith&quot; vs. Mathir. And keep looking at those AC 51 BP's you can make with Cultural v2. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Overall, these are good changes, as we'll now be able to level up smithing with items that are usable at earlier levels, so more banded and FS armor will be around I think. The Test Server people are still giving Yak feedback on the levels and the progression, but I'm pretty sure it won't seriously effect my analysis, at least for my toons. <br>
<br>
My advice? If you are mid-banded, level up past it if you can spare the plat. It will get &gt;&gt;much&lt;&lt; more expensive to raise after this goes in. If you are only semi-serious about smithing, no real need to get your panties in a twist and just wait and see what happens. <br>
<br>
If you are low level, unless you have the money to blow to get to 175, just wait for the trivials to be lowered, and you should be able to level up with more usable items. Although keep in mind that others will be doing the same, so it will still likely be very annoying to watch the market readjust. No telling if the &quot;easy&quot; stuff (metal bits items to 135) will still be there or moved down as well. Time will tell. <br>
<br>
Finally, being in a race with cultural smithing is more and more important if you want to smith higher than FS: Wood Elves, Erudites and Halflings have Cultural Tailoring as their &quot;thing&quot; so if you want to smith with one of those races, you will be fighting an uphill battle. Not impossible, just harder. And the top end smithing stuff will not be available to you. Vah Shir and Half Elves are very much out of luck as they don't have any cultural stuff of any stripe. (!) Trolls have some cultural smithing, but it's looking to be weapons only. <br>
<br>
Choose wisely!<br>
<br>
Exciting times ahead! <br>
<br>
